Chairman/Chief Executive Officer of National Hajj Commission (NAHCON) Alhaji Kunle Hassan has inaugurated the medical team for this year’s hajj. The 15-man team’s inauguration followed the screening and orientation of applicants for 2022 National Medical Team (NMT). NAHCON’s Commissioner for Planning, Research, Statistics, and Library Studies (PRSLS) Suleiman Momoh, will head the team while Zainab Sheriff, a pharmacist is the team’s coordinator.   ‘Agroforestry, land use policy to address land degradation’     Group advises APC on choice of presidential candidate     ‘Resolve ASUU strike or face protest worse than…   Hassan urged them to distinguish themselves in the discharge of their responsibilities, saying indiscipline will not be condoned. Momoh assured them of the commission’s commitment to the success of the team. He enjoined them to make NAHCON and Nigeria proud as one of the best medical teams in this Hajj season. Shariff congratulated members for being among the few to be selected for the Hajj exercise. She urged them to deliver quality service to the pilgrims who they will be engaged to serve. She called for team-work among members, reminding them that the commission shall not compromise on discipline.